M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: CRITICAL**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Waterfalls are the #1 performance killer. Each sequential await adds full network latency. Eliminating them yields the largest gains.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: HIGH (avoids unnecessary async work when a synchronous guard already fails)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|When a branch uses `await` for a flag or remote value and also requires a **cheap synchronous** condition (local props, request metadata, already-loaded state), evaluate the cheap condition **first**.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|This is a specialization of [Defer Await Until Needed](./async-defer-await.md) for `flag && cheapCondition` style checks.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const someFlag = await getFlag()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (someFlag && someCondition) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// ...
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (someCondition) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const someFlag = await getFlag()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (someFlag) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// ...
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|This matters when `getFlag` hits the network, a feature-flag service, or `React.cache` / DB work: skipping it when `someCondition` is false removes that cost on the cold path.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Keep the original order if `someCondition` is expensive, depends on the flag, or you must run side effects in a fixed order.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: HIGH (avoids blocking unused code paths)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Move `await` operations into the branches where they're actually used to avoid blocking code paths that don't need them.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: blocks both branches**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function handleRequest(userId: string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (skipProcessing) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Returns immediately but still waited for userData
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return { skipped: true }
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Only this branch uses userData
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return processUserData(userData)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: only blocks when needed**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function handleRequest(userId: string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (skipProcessing) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Returns immediately without waiting
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return { skipped: true }
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Fetch only when needed
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return processUserData(userData)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Another example: early return optimization**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Incorrect: always fetches permissions
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function updateResource(resourceId: string, userId: string) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (!resource) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return { error: 'Not found' }
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return { error: 'Forbidden' }
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Correct: fetches only when needed
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function updateResource(resourceId: string, userId: string) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (!resource) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return { error: 'Not found' }
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return { error: 'Forbidden' }
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|This optimization is especially valuable when the skipped branch is frequently taken, or when the deferred operation is expensive.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|For `await getFlag()` combined with a cheap synchronous guard (`flag && someCondition`), see [Check Cheap Conditions Before Async Flags](./async-cheap-condition-before-await.md).
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: CRITICAL (2-10× improvement)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|For operations with partial dependencies, use `better-all` to maximize parallelism. It automatically starts each task at the earliest possible moment.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: profile waits for config unnecessarily**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const [user, config] = await Promise.all([
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchUser(),
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchConfig()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const profile = await fetchProfile(user.id)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: config and profile run in parallel**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|import { all } from 'better-all'
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const { user, config, profile } = await all({
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async user() { return fetchUser() },
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async config() { return fetchConfig() },
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async profile() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return fetchProfile((await this.$.user).id)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|})
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Alternative without extra dependencies:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const userPromise = fetchUser()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const profilePromise = userPromise.then(user => fetchProfile(user.id))
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const [user, config, profile] = await Promise.all([
M|vercel-react-best-practices|userPromise,
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchConfig(),
M|vercel-react-best-practices|profilePromise
M|vercel-react-best-practices|])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|We can also create all the promises first, and do `Promise.all()` at the end.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference: [https://github.com/shuding/better-all](https://github.com/shuding/better-all)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: CRITICAL (2-10× improvement)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|In API routes and Server Actions, start independent operations immediately, even if you don't await them yet.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: config waits for auth, data waits for both**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const ses = await auth()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const config = await fetchConfig()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const data = await fetchData(ses.user.id)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return rsp.json({ data, config })
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: auth and config start immediately**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const sessionPromise = auth()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const configPromise = fetchConfig()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const ses = await sessionPromise
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const [config, data] = await Promise.all([
M|vercel-react-best-practices|configPromise,
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchData(ses.user.id)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return rsp.json({ data, config })
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|For operations with more complex dependency chains, use `better-all` to automatically maximize parallelism (see Dependency-Based Parallelization).
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: CRITICAL (2-10× improvement)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|When async operations have no interdependencies, execute them concurrently using `Promise.all()`.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: sequential execution, 3 round trips**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const user = await fetchUser()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const posts = await fetchPosts()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const comments = await fetchComments()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: parallel execution, 1 round trip**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const [user, posts, comments] = await Promise.all([
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchUser(),
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchPosts(),
M|vercel-react-best-practices|fetchComments()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: HIGH (faster initial paint)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Instead of awaiting data in async components before returning JSX, use Suspense boundaries to show the wrapper UI faster while data loads.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: wrapper blocked by data fetching**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function Page() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const data = await fetchData() // Blocks entire page
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return (
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Header</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<DataDisplay data={data} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Footer</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|The entire layout waits for data even though only the middle section needs it.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: wrapper shows immediately, data streams in**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|function Page() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return (
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Header</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<DataDisplay />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|</Suspense>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Footer</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function DataDisplay() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const data = await fetchData() // Only blocks this component
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return <div>{data.cnt}</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Sidebar, Header, and Footer render immediately. Only DataDisplay waits for data.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Alternative: share promise across components**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|function Page() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Start fetch immediately, but don't await
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const dataPromise = fetchData()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return (
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<div>Header</div>
