M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference: [https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/authentication](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/authentication)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: LOW (reduces network payload by avoiding duplicate serialization)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|RSC→client serialization deduplicates by object reference, not value. Same reference = serialized once; new reference = serialized again. Do transformations (`.toSorted()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`) in c
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: duplicates array**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// RSC: sends 6 strings (2 arrays × 3 items)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<ClientList usernames={usernames} usernamesOrdered={usernames.toSorted()} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: sends 3 strings**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// RSC: send once
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<ClientList usernames={usernames} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Client: transform there
M|vercel-react-best-practices|'use client'
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const sorted = useMemo(() => [...usernames].sort(), [usernames])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Nested deduplication behavior:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// string[] - duplicates everything
M|vercel-react-best-practices|usernames={['a','b']} sorted={usernames.toSorted()} // sends 4 strings
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// object[] - duplicates array structure only
M|vercel-react-best-practices|users={[{id:1},{id:2}]} sorted={users.toSorted()} // sends 2 arrays + 2 unique objects (not 4)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Deduplication works recursively. Impact varies by data type:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `string[]`, `number[]`, `boolean[]`: **HIGH impact** - array + all primitives fully duplicated
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `object[]`: **LOW impact** - array duplicated, but nested objects deduplicated by reference
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Operations breaking deduplication: create new references**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Arrays: `.toSorted()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`, `.slice()`, `[...arr]`
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Objects: `{...obj}`, `Object.assign()`, `structuredClone()`, `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify())`
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**More examples:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// ❌ Bad
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<C users={users} active={users.filter(u => u.active)} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<C product={product} productName={product.name} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// ✅ Good
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<C users={users} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|<C product={product} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Do filtering/destructuring in client
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Exception:** Pass derived data when transformation is expensive or client doesn't need original.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: HIGH (prevents concurrency bugs and request data leaks)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|For React Server Components and client components rendered during SSR, avoid using mutable module-level variables to share request-scoped data. Server renders can run concurrently in the same process.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Treat module scope on the server as process-wide shared mem, not request-local state.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: request data leaks across concurrent renders**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|let currentUser: User | null = null
M|vercel-react-best-practices|export default async function Page() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|currentUser = await auth()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return <Dashboard />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|async function Dashboard() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return <div>{currentUser?.name}</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|If two requests overlap, request A can set `currentUser`, then request B overwrites it before request A finishes rendering `Dashboard`.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: keep request data local to the render tree**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|export default async function Page() {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const user = await auth()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return <Dashboard user={user} />
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|function Dashboard({ user }: { user: User | null }) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return <div>{user?.name}</div>
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Safe exceptions:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Immutable static assets or config loaded once at module scope
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Shared caches intentionally designed for cross-request reuse and keyed correctly
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Process-wide singletons that do not store request- or user-specific mutable data
M|vercel-react-best-practices|For static assets and config, see [Hoist Static I/O to Module Level](./server-hoist-static-io.md).
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: HIGH (caches across requests)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|`React.cache()` only works within one request. For data shared across sequential requests (user clicks button A then button B), use an LRU cache.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Implementation:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|import { LRUCache } from 'lru-cache'
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const cache = new LRUCache<string, any>({
M|vercel-react-best-practices|max: 1000,
M|vercel-react-best-practices|ttl: 5 * 60 * 1000  // 5 minutes
M|vercel-react-best-practices|})
M|vercel-react-best-practices|export async function getUser(id: string) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const cached = cache.get(id)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|if (cached) return cached
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const user = await db.user.findUnique({ where: { id } })
M|vercel-react-best-practices|cache.set(id, user)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return user
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Request 1: DB query, result cached
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Request 2: cache hit, no DB query
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Use when sequential user actions hit multiple endpoints needing the same data within seconds.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**With Vercel's [Fluid Compute](https://vercel.com/docs/fluid-compute):** LRU caching is especially effective because multiple concurrent requests can share the same function instance and cache. This 
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**In traditional serverless:** Each invocation runs in isolation, so consider Redis for cross-process caching.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference: [https://github.com/isaacs/node-lru-cache](https://github.com/isaacs/node-lru-cache)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: HIGH (avoids repeated file/network I/O per request)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|When loading static assets (fonts, logos, images, config files) in route handlers or server functions, hoist the I/O operation to module level. Module-level code runs once when the module is first imp
