M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Next.js-Specific Note:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|In Next.js, the `fetch` API is automatically extended with request memoization. Requests with the same URL and options are automatically deduplicated within a single request, so you don't need `React.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Database queries (Prisma, Drizzle, etc.)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Heavy computations
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Authentication checks
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- File system operations
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Any non-fetch async work
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Use `React.cache()` to deduplicate these operations across your component tree.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference: [https://react.dev/reference/react/cache](https://react.dev/reference/react/cache)
