M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Benefits:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|1. **Stable callback references** - Callbacks don't need to be recreated when state changes
M|vercel-react-best-practices|2. **No stale closures** - Always operates on the latest state value
M|vercel-react-best-practices|3. **Fewer dependencies** - Simplifies dependency arrays and reduces mem leaks
M|vercel-react-best-practices|4. **Prevents bugs** - Eliminates the most common source of React closure bugs
