M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Why this matters in React:**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|1. Props/state mutations break React's immutability model - React expects props and state to be treated as read-only
M|vercel-react-best-practices|2. Causes stale closure bugs - Mutating arrays inside closures (callbacks, effects) can lead to unexpected behavior
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Browser support: fallback for older browsers**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
