M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: LOW (avoids unnecessary effect re-runs and lint errors)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Effect Event functions do not have a stable identity. Their identity intentionally changes on every render. Do not include the function returned by `useEffectEvent` in a `useEffect` dependency array. 
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: Effect Event added as a dependency**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'react'
M|vercel-react-best-practices|function ChatRoom({ roomId, onConnected }: {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|roomId: string
M|vercel-react-best-practices|onConnected: () => void
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|useEffect(() => {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|connection.connect()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}, [roomId, handleConnected])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Including the Effect Event in dependencies makes the effect re-run every render and triggers the React Hooks lint rule.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct: depend on reactive values, not the Effect Event**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```tsx
M|vercel-react-best-practices|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'react'
M|vercel-react-best-practices|function ChatRoom({ roomId, onConnected }: {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|roomId: string
M|vercel-react-best-practices|onConnected: () => void
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}) {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|useEffect(() => {
M|vercel-react-best-practices|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|connection.connect()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}, [roomId])
M|vercel-react-best-practices|}
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference: [https://react.dev/reference/react/useEffectEvent#effect-event-in-deps](https://react.dev/reference/react/useEffectEvent#effect-event-in-deps)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Impact: LOW-MEDIUM (avoids duplicate init in dev)**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Do not put app-wide initialization that must run once per app load inside `useEffect([])` of a component. Components can remount and effects will re-run. Use a module-level guard or top-level init in 
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect: runs twice in dev, re-runs on remount**
